node.contents: One problem I see here is that it appears you have at least one non-UI thread ("Smack Listener Processor (1)") accessing UI components. Remember that Swing is not thread-safe, and weird things start happening when you access Swing components off the Event Dispatch Thread.

node.contents: Looks like you are doing Swing/AWT operations in the Smack Listener Thread. Swing is not thread-safe, so you need to do all Swing operations in the AWT-EventQueue-0 thread.
